headline: Stock Market Today: Dow Climbs 664 Points, Revisits 47,000; Nvidia Falls As Palantir Rises (Live Coverage)
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average and other major indexes ended Tuesday with hefty gains, as investors saw weak economic data as supporting a decision by the Federal Reserve to lower interest rates in December.  Nvidia and Advanced Micro Devices slid on the stock market today on a report that Meta Platforms will use Google's AI chips.  The Dow closed up 1.4%, or 664 points, despite Nvidia's 2.6% drop.

headline: Stock Market Today: Dow Jumps On Rate-Cut Prospects; Cruise Line Name Sails Into Buy Zone (Live Coverage)
summary: Gains on the Dow Jones Industrial Average and other major indexes revved up Tuesday afternoon, as investors anticipated that a round of weak economic data would help convince the Federal Reserve to cut interest rates in December.  Nvidia and Advanced Micro Devices sold off on the stock market today on a report that Meta Platforms will use Google's AI chips.  The Dow picked up momentum and rallied 1.2%, or about 550 points, despite Nvidia's more than 3% drop.

summary: Dick's Sporting Goods acquired Foot Locker for $2.4 billion. To ensure the tie-up doesn't become a drag on profits, the company is shrinking its footprint.

headline: DICK'S Sporting Goods Names Matthew Barnes President, Foot Locker International
summary: DICK'S Sporting Goods today announced the appointment of Matthew Barnes as President of Foot Locker International, effective December 3, 2025. Barnes will lead the Foot Locker business' international operations with a focus on driving strategic growth, accelerating business momentum and executing targeted turnaround strategies.
